---
import MarketingLayout from '../../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
import PackageLadder from '../../components/sections/PackageLadder.astro';
import { sitePath } from '../../lib/paths';
import { copywritingAddOns } from '../../data/offer-site';
---
<MarketingLayout title="Pricing | Website Factory" description="Professional local business website packages starting at $3,500.">
  <section class="content-section"><div class="container prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
    <h1>Professional Website Launch - starting at $3,500</h1>
    <p>A clear anchor package for businesses that need more than a starter page and less than a bloated agency engagement.</p>
  </div></section>

  <PackageLadder heading="Choose the right launch path" intro="Starter, Professional, Custom Layout, and Monthly Care are separate offers with different levels of strategy, design translation, and ongoing support." />

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container comparison-section" aria-labelledby="starter-vs-professional">
      <p class="eyebrow">Starter Credibility Site vs. Professional Launch</p>
      <h2 id="starter-vs-professional">Starter makes you credible online. Professional helps customers understand, trust, and choose you.</h2>
      <p class="comparison-intro">Starter is the fast credibility move. Professional is for owners who need the website to explain value, handle objections, and make a higher-value service feel easier to choose.</p>
      <div class="comparison-grid">
        <article class="comparison-card starter">
          <h3>Starter Credibility Site</h3>
          <p>Best for businesses that need a clean, credible web presence quickly.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>4-5 core pages</li>
            <li>Basic service descriptions</li>
            <li>Mobile-friendly layout</li>
            <li>Contact page and call-to-action</li>
            <li>Basic local SEO structure</li>
            <li>Simple trust and credibility layout</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="comparison-card professional">
          <h3>Professional Website Launch</h3>
          <p>Best for businesses that need the site to explain, persuade, and build trust.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Expanded service copy</li>
            <li>Stronger homepage positioning</li>
            <li>FAQs that answer customer objections</li>
            <li>Testimonials or proof sections</li>
            <li>Gallery or before/after structure</li>
            <li>Service-area messaging</li>
            <li>More polished conversion flow</li>
            <li>Better suited for businesses trying to justify higher-value services</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section muted-bg">
    <div class="container two-col">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Custom layout</p>
        <h2>Have a sketch or custom layout?</h2>
        <p>Sketches, mood boards, and custom page structures are welcome, but they move the project into the Custom Layout Build tier. That work requires custom design translation instead of the standard launch system.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="premium-card">
        <h3>What changes in scope</h3>
        <p>Custom layout projects include layout planning, responsive interpretation, translation from rough direction into buildable sections, and extra QA for pages that do not follow the standard template structure.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Copywriting add-on</p>
      <h2>What if the website copy is not ready?</h2>
      <p>If you already have usable copy, we polish and place it. If you have rough notes, we can turn those notes into website-ready pages. If there is no usable copy yet, deeper copywriting and positioning can be added to the project.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container pricing-grid">
      {copywritingAddOns.map((item) => (
        <article class="price-card">
          <span>Copy support</span>
          <h3>{item.name}</h3>
          <strong>{item.price}</strong>
          <p>{item.description}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
    <div class="container copy-note">
      <p>Final copywriting scope depends on how much accurate raw material you provide. We do not invent credentials, guarantees, licenses, years in business, or claims you have not confirmed. Client review and fact-checking are required before launch.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>How pricing is finalized</h2>
      <p>Final pricing is confirmed after intake based on page count, copy depth, asset readiness, special layout needs, and revision scope. You will know the project range before work begins.</p>
      <p><a class="button-primary" href={sitePath('offer-site/contact')}>Start Project Intake</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
